- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The efficiency analysis of the proposed method involves the study of the growth rate of its computational complexity, which is a typical topic in numerical analysis. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The non-polynomial growth rate of the proposed method's efficiency may also be of interest to researchers in this sub-category, which deals with the study of the intrinsic difficulty of computational problems.
